ATM Simulator in C++
Description
A simple C++ program that simulates basic ATM functionalities such as account creation, secure login, balance inquiry, deposits, and withdrawals through a menu-driven interface.

Features
Secure login with username and password.
View balance, deposit, and withdraw money.
Simple and user-friendly menu system.
How to Run
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/ATM-Simulator.git
Compile the code:
bash
Copy code
g++ ATM.cpp -o ATM
Run the program:
bash
Copy code
./ATM
Example Usage
Setup Account: Create a username and password.
Login: Enter your credentials to access the menu.
Menu Options:
1: Check balance
2: Deposit money
3: Withdraw money
4: Exit
Future Enhancements
Add transaction history.
Enable multi-user support.
Implement password masking and persistent data storage.
